# Copy this file to `.bazelrc.remote`. Do not commit the copied file.
#
# Managed remote cache is opt-in because credentials, write policy, and cache
# ownership must be explicit. Bazel's remote cache stores action outputs keyed by
# action inputs, so cache writes should be enabled only for trusted branches or
# trusted CI identities.
#
# Example shape:
#
# build --remote_cache=https://remote-cache.example.invalid
# build --remote_timeout=60s
# build --remote_header=x-cache-api-key=${BAZEL_REMOTE_CACHE_TOKEN}
#
# Developers usually read from the cache but do not upload by default:
#
# build --noremote_upload_local_results
#
# Trusted CI can opt into uploads by uncommenting this in its generated remote
# rc file:
#
# build:ci --remote_upload_local_results
# test:ci --remote_upload_local_results
